CONFIRMED genuine skip (#3) — needs the removed `py=` Python remap BODY.

test.ini remaps with a pure Python body: `REMAP=M400 modalgroup=5 py=interp_error`,
where interp_error() calls self.set_errormsg(...) and returns INTERP_ERROR. gomc
rejects `py=`/`python=` remaps outright at parse ("python= remaps have been
removed. Use ngc= with prolog/epilog cmod handlers"), so a py= body cannot run.

The capability this exercises — a failing remap handler must abort and convey its
error text — is already re-expressed for the C mechanism in remap/fail/prolog and
remap/fail/epilog (interp_ext set_error + INTERP_EXT_ERROR; see DISPOSITION §2e).
Only the `py=` body form itself is removed (its gomc replacement is an `ngc=` body,
which cannot "return INTERP_ERROR" as a Python body did). Genuine removal.
